{'Fund': 'Debit Card e-Mandate
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Debit Card e-Mandate
;
Fund DetailBank has introduced facility of registering for E-mandate / standing instruction / recurring payment instruction through Bank of Baroda VISA and MasterCard Debit Card variants. Bank of Baroda Debit Card holders can register for e-Mandates on a merchant platforms for recurring transactions e.g. e-Mandate set at telecom service provider, OTT platforms, insurance partners and other utility service providers like electricity, gas, water, etc. This facility has been provided by the Bank in accordance with the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) regulations on Processing of e-Mandate on cards for recurring transactions, as amended from time to time and effective October 1st, 2021.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Debit Card e-Mandate : Transaction Limits
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Debit Card e-Mandate : Transaction Limits
;
Fund DetailPer transaction limit up to 15,000/-, does not require AFA (OTP authentication process) for subsequent transactions.
Any subsequent transactions >15,000/- or above the limit set by the cardholder, AFA (OTP authentication process) is required.
Note: The maximum limit of recurring transactions will be as per limit defined by the Bank for ecommerce transactions for respective card variant.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Debit Card e-Mandate : Fees & Charges
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Debit Card e-Mandate : Fees & Charges
;
Fund DetailBank is not charging any fees for availing e-Mandate facility through Debit Cards', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Tokenisation : Features
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Tokenisation : Features
;
Fund DetailCard details cannot be saved by merchants Payment Gateway.
Mode of Payment- Token assigned to a card.
Different Token for different platforms', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Tokenisation : Eligibility Criteria and Tokenisation : Fees & Charges

', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Tokenisation : Eligibility Criteria and Tokenisation : Fees & Charges

;
Fund DetailFor all Card variants.
The customer need not pay any charges for availing the service of Tokenising the card.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Tokenisation : Most Important Terms and Conditions (MITC)
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Tokenisation : Most Important Terms and Conditions (MITC)
;
Fund DetailRBI has directed the payment aggregators, wallets and online merchants (entities in card transaction/payment chain other than card issuers/card networks) to not store any sensitive card related customer information including full card details. Hence, the card details can be replaced with tokens. Please be assured that this will not hamper your card transaction experience but will make your card transactions more secure.
The Debit card shall be tokenised at the Ecommerce merchant website/ Mobile application. Customer consent would be obtained from the customer by the Ecommerce merchant along with OTP authentication prior to Debit card tokenisation.
Post 30th September 2022, all cards needs to be tokenized.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'FASTag
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: FASTag
;
Fund DetailFASTag is an easy-to-use reloadable tag that enables automatic deduction of toll charges instead of paying cash at toll booths. Employing Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) technology, FASTag enables contactless toll collection. The toll charges are automatically deducted from the linked prepaid account by affixing a tag to the vehicle’s windshield.
To reduce vehicular traffic and congestion on national highways, the National Highways Authority of India (NHAI) & Indian Highways Management Company Limited (IHMCL) authorized the National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI) to provide a contactless solution for toll collection. FASTag is a Government-led initiative that allows vehicles to pass through the toll booth hassle-free without stopping.
You can apply online to open a Baroda FASTag prepaid account in no-time. On approval, the bank issues unique RFID tags for your vehicle. All you need to do is affix the tag, add funds to the prepaid account, and you are ready to travel cashless across India’s national highways. ', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is Electronic Toll Collection (ETC)/Baroda FASTag?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is Electronic Toll Collection (ETC)/Baroda FASTag?
;
Fund DetailElectronic Toll Collection is a solution for digital payment of toll charges using FASTag. Baroda FASTag is a device that employs Radio Frequency Identification (RFID) technology for making toll payments directly from the prepaid account linked to it. It is affixed on the windscreen of your vehicle and enables you to drive through toll plazas. Baroda FASTag has a validity of 5 years and after purchasing it, you only need to recharge/top-up the FASTag as per your requirement.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What are the documents required to apply for FASTag?', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What are the documents required to apply for FASTag?;
Fund DetailYou need to submit the following documents:

Registration Certificate (RC) of the vehicle
FASTag Application form
Aadhaar Card/Driving License/PAN Card/Voter ID Card/Passport', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'I have two vehicles - can I use one FASTag for two cars?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: I have two vehicles - can I use one FASTag for two cars?
;
Fund DetailNo. You will need to take two individual FASTags, one for each of the two vehicles.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is the validity period of the FASTag card?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is the validity period of the FASTag card?
;
Fund DetailThe tag has a validity of 5 years.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What happens if there is an incorrect deduction from my FASTag account?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What happens if there is an incorrect deduction from my FASTag account?
;
Fund DetailYou need not worry. In case you find an inappropriate debit to your account, report it on complaints sanction of portal immediately. Please ensure that your RC copy of vehicle is uploaded in portal. On receipt the complaint we will take up the matter with issuer bank and try to get it resolved in 15 days maximum. Log in to portal for logging the complaint here.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'I was not allowed to go through the FASTag lane despite having an active FASTag account with sufficient balance. How do I fix this issue?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: I was not allowed to go through the FASTag lane despite having an active FASTag account with sufficient balance. How do I fix this issue?
;
Fund DetailYou can raise a request regarding the same by calling the customer care at 1800-103-4568 or email on barodafastag@tollplus.com. We will look into the matter and resolve it as soon as possible.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I avail a monthly pass?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I avail a monthly pass?
;
Fund DetailYes, you can avail the monthly pass from the NHAI website, and the facility is specific to each toll plaza.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What happens in case I lose my RFID Tag? Will the funds in the wallet be lost too?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What happens in case I lose my RFID Tag? Will the funds in the wallet be lost too?
;
Fund DetailCall our customer care number at 1800-103-4568 immediately to block your FASTag. You can visit any of Bank of Baroda branch and request re-issue of the tag. The bank will transfer any balance linked to the old account to your current account.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Why are the toll rates different for different vehicle categories?', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Why are the toll rates different for different vehicle categories?;
Fund DetailToll rates are categorized basis the vehicle size and load. Depending on these two factors, the damage done to the road and type of use (commercial/personal) of a vehicle, the toll rates are determined. The same toll rates will be deducted using FASTag too.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Where all can I commute using FASTag? Is it available in all highways?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Where all can I commute using FASTag? Is it available in all highways?
;
Fund DetailAs per the Govt. of India mandate, all the toll plazas must have the acquiring system to read the FASTag technology, and if it is not available at toll plazas vehicles affixed with FASTag can move without paying the toll charges.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Which are the roads where Baroda FASTag can be used?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Which are the roads where Baroda FASTag can be used?
;
Fund DetailBaroda FASTag can be used on all toll plazas on National Highways where it has been integrated. To find out list of toll plazas currently integrated with FASTag, kindly visit NHAI site at http://www.nhai.org

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How can I recharge my Baroda FASTag account?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How can I recharge my Baroda FASTag account?
;
Fund DetailYou may recharge your account by cash, at the Point of Sale (POS) locations or you may also recharge online through debit/credit card or through net banking.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How do I generate/reset my username and password?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How do I generate/reset my username and password?
;
Fund DetailPlease log in to the customer portal and register yourself to generate your User ID and password. Please enter the required information in the prompts and the system will send an SMS with your log in details to your registered mobile number. You may call our customer care number: 18001034560 for assistance.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can a Baroda FASTag bought for my one vehicle be used for another vehicle?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can a Baroda FASTag bought for my one vehicle be used for another vehicle?
;
Fund DetailNo, Baroda FASTag is issued to each vehicle based on KYC (Know Your Customer) documents submitted. If a Baroda FASTag, for instance, bought for one car is used for a truck then such FASTag shall get blacklisted resulting into denial of vehicle passage from FASTag lanes on toll plazas. Baroda FASTag users are advised to desist from such practice.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Doorstep Banking
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Doorstep Banking
;
Fund DetailDoorstep Banking is one of the key action points of the roadmap for banking reforms under the EASE (Enhanced Access & Service Excellence) reforms brought out by the Department of Financial Services. PSB Alliance Doorstep Banking Service is a facility introduced in this regard to cater to both financial and non-financial banking needs of the customers of all Banks under a single umbrella.
Bank of Baroda is one of the member Banks under the PSB Alliance Door Step Banking initiative taken by PSB Alliance through which customers can avail major Banking transaction services at their Door Step. It shall be implemented by Door Step Banking(DSB) agents in 100 major Centers across the Country for offering different financial as well as non financial services.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'ATMs : Overview
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: ATMs : Overview
;
Fund DetailThere are more than 9,200 ATMs set-up within India- With this we ensure that you are never too far from an ATM. User-friendly graphic screen and easy to follow instructions in a language of your choice makes our ATM Banking a smooth experience. Bank of Baroda has partnered with National Financial Switch (NFS), Visa, MasterCard, Discover, JCB and UnionPay, Therefore, Debit/ATM card issued by members of NFS, Visa and MasterCard, Discover, JCB and UnionPay cards are accepted at our all ATMs.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Cash Recyclers (CRs) : Overview
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Cash Recyclers (CRs) : Overview
;
Fund DetailThe Cash Recycler machine (CR) is a self-service terminal that lets you and me to make deposit and withdrawal transactions of cash. All successful transactions are immediately credited or debited in real time and customers will be issued an acknowledgment slip confirming the transaction.                                                        A person having debit card can use the CR machine for withdrawal, however, to use the CR machine for depositing the cash, customers need to have either his/her Bank of Baroda debit card or to know beneficiary’s account number in Bank of Baroda. The transaction receipt also gives you your updated account balance.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Cash Recyclers (CRs) : Talking Cash Recyclers for visually challenged person
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Cash Recyclers (CRs) : Talking Cash Recyclers for visually challenged person
;
Fund DetailTalking Cash Recyclers for visually challenged person
Talking Cash Recyclers provide financial access to blind persons in deposit/withdrawal cash on their own, anytime, and provides greater banking usability for the low vision, illiterate and aged population.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is a Credit Card?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is a Credit Card?
;
Fund DetailA credit card is a financial instrument supplied by banks with a pre-set credit limit for online and offline shopping. You may be eligible for a credit card based on your credit score, history, income, and other bank guidelines. Apply for a credit card at BOB Financial site. In other words, a credit card is your convenient, anytime money that you must repay only after 50 days because there is no interest until then.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How to check Credit Card Eligibility?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How to check Credit Card Eligibility?
;
Fund DetailVisit our website at www.bobfinancial.com to check your eligibility and apply for your Bank of Baroda credit card.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How many credit cards can I have?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How many credit cards can I have?
;
Fund DetailUsually, banks offer 1 credit card to every customer, few banks also offer multiple credit cards to the same customer. For ex: Retail Card for personal use and Business or Corporate Credit Card for official expenses.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I pay a person with a credit card?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I pay a person with a credit card?
;
Fund DetailPayments by credit cards are not permitted for P2P transactions. However, credit card loans are available. (Conditions apply)

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I transfer money from credit card to bank account?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I transfer money from credit card to bank account?
;
Fund DetailNo. Certain credit card transactions are not permitted, and one of them is the transfer of funds to a bank account.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How much cash can I withdraw from credit card?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How much cash can I withdraw from credit card?
;
Fund DetailEvery card comes with a sub-limit for cash withdrawals, you can use your card up to that amount for cash withdrawal at the ATM using your credit card. You can confirm your cash limit by calling customer service number printed on your credit card.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'When can I redeem my credit card reward points?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: When can I redeem my credit card reward points?
;
Fund DetailEvery card has a cash withdrawal sub-limit. You can use your credit card to withdraw cash from an ATM up to that amount. Call the customer support number on the back of your credit card to confirm your cash limit.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How do I increase my credit card limit?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How do I increase my credit card limit?
;
Fund DetailYou can call the customer support number on your credit card to see if you are qualified for a higher limit or to learn how to request one.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How is my credit card limit decided?
', 'Fund Detail': "Fund: How is my credit card limit decided?
;
Fund DetailThe bank determines the credit card limit based on one's income, existing debts, and performance on past repayments (if any).

", 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'bob World UPI
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: bob World UPI
;
Fund DetailBank of Baroda presents bob World UPI - A Unified Payments Interface (UPI) application that lets you transfer funds from any bank account using a Virtual Payment Address (VPA). No need to remember beneficiary details like account number, IFSC, Mobile Number, MMID etc. Send or Collect money using a Virtual Payment Address.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'bob World UPI : Most Important Terms and Conditions (MITC)
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: bob World UPI : Most Important Terms and Conditions (MITC)
;
Fund DetailTo check out the privacy policy, please click here', 'file_chunk_index': 2}

{'Fund': 'What is Unified Payment Interface?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is Unified Payment Interface?
;
Fund DetailUnified payment Interface (UPI) is a payment system developed by National Payment Corporation of India (NPCI). It is a platform where customer can fetch and place all his accounts maintained with different banks and transact through these accounts. UPI allows you to transfer money between any two parties via smart phone through a payment identifier like virtual payment address or Account number + IFSC.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Who started it/who is behind it?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Who started it/who is behind it?
;
Fund DetailUPI is an initiative of National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI).

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is NPCI?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is NPCI?
;
Fund DetailNPCI is the National Payments Corporation of India. They run a lot of the payments infrastructure in India, including issuing RuPay Cards and making sure you can withdraw money from any ATM irrespective of the bank.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Which phones/platforms are supported by these UPI Applications?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Which phones/platforms are supported by these UPI Applications?
;
Fund DetailPresently, BHIM Baroda Pay application supports Android Mobile and iOS platform phones.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I access these UPI Applications from my computer?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I access these UPI Applications from my computer?
;
Fund DetailNo, presently UPI applications are available only through mobile application and is not accessible from your computer.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Do I Need Mobile Internet for downloading and using the application?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Do I Need Mobile Internet for downloading and using the application?
;
Fund DetailYes, you need a basic mobile internet/GPRS to download these applications. You will need to have an active mobile Internet service to be able to use these applications and its features.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How much does it cost to use BHIM Baroda Pay UPI?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How much does it cost to use BHIM Baroda Pay UPI?
;
Fund DetailBHIM Baroda Pay UPI can be downloaded for free. The Mobile App uses mobile internet data and messaging that will incur charges based on your telecom providers data and messaging plan.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Do I need to register for making transactions using UPI?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Do I need to register for making transactions using UPI?
;
Fund DetailYes, you need to register on UPI and link your bank accounts before performing transactions.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Is it mandatory to have an Account with Bank of Baroda, Dena Bank or Vijay Bank to use the respective UPI Applications of these Banks?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Is it mandatory to have an Account with Bank of Baroda, Dena Bank or Vijay Bank to use the respective UPI Applications of these Banks?
;
Fund DetailNo, A person who is having an account eligible for UPI Applications with any Bank, can use any of these UPI applications. However, the user must have an account with a UPI enabled Bank, updated list of which are available on NPCI website.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I use BHIM Baroda Pay when I am travelling abroad?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I use BHIM Baroda Pay when I am travelling abroad?
;
Fund DetailBHIM Baroda Pay has been enabled for use in India as well as aboard/overseas (roaming facility on same number will be enabled).

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How BHIM Baroda Pay UPI is beneficial over mobile banking?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How BHIM Baroda Pay UPI is beneficial over mobile banking?
;
Fund DetailAll Banks have their own mobile banking App. When a user has accounts in multiple Banks, he/she has to download the Mobile Banking Application of all those banks. Whereas in UPI, any Bank Customer may download and use the UPI App of any Bank live with UPI. Hence, a user may transact from any Bank account on one platform that is UPI. Easy self-registration by downloading application from Play Store/App store.
The service is instant and available 24X7, even on public/bank holidays. Also, there is no pre-registration required for the beneficiary.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I have more than one UPI Application?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I have more than one UPI Application?
;
Fund DetailYes, you can have multiple UPI Apps of different Bank with same mobile number registered with respective bank accounts.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How to set Login PIN?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How to set Login PIN?
;
Fund DetailYou can set Login PIN of your choice in the below format Bank of Baroda - 4-character Login PIN.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How can I add more Bank Account after successful creation of Profile?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How can I add more Bank Account after successful creation of Profile?
;
Fund DetailAfter successful registration with UPI, click on Add Bank Account. Choose your bank from the list in which this mobile number is updated. Application will fetch the eligible account number link with the same mobile number.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is UPI PIN and how to set it?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is UPI PIN and how to set it?
;
Fund DetailUPI PIN is a second factor authentication i.e., 4 Digit transaction PIN which is required to authorize financial and non-financial transactions. Debit Card is mandatory for Setting UPI PIN.UPI PIN can be set by entering last 6 six digits of debit card and expiry date along with OTP delivered to your registered mobile number from issuer bank. You can use Change PIN option to change the PIN required for transactions. Bank of Baroda-4 Digit UPI PIN (All Link Account number will have Same UPI PIN).

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Why am I not able to set UPI PIN for my account despite entering valid debit card details?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Why am I not able to set UPI PIN for my account despite entering valid debit card details?
;
Fund DetailUsing the active debit card, you can set the UPI PIN only for the account linked to the card. In case of card is not linked to account, please contact your branch.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How many Bank Accounts can I add to my Profile?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How many Bank Accounts can I add to my Profile?
;
Fund DetailYou can add below numbers of eligible accounts in your profile. You can click on plus, under UPI Accounts or go to Manage Accounts and proceed for adding Bank accounts.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is Virtual Payment Address (VPA)?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is Virtual Payment Address (VPA)?
;
Fund Detail
Virtual Payment Address is created for your bank account which acts as a unique identifier to be used for performing the transactions. To send money, you just need to enter the virtual address of the beneficiary. The beneficiary need not to share account details as only VPA is required for transaction. There will be different VPA handler for the different Bank like -
For Bank of Baroda handler is - @barodapay and @barodampay', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How many Virtual Payment Addresses can be created against one Bank Account?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How many Virtual Payment Addresses can be created against one Bank Account?
;
Fund DetailYou can create maximum 3+1 Virtual Payment Addresses. The created VPA must be linked with one account to receive payments. The Payment will be received on Default account number set for respective VPA

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'How many Bank Accounts can be linked with one Virtual Payment Address?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: How many Bank Accounts can be linked with one Virtual Payment Address?
;
Fund DetailYou can link multiple Bank Accounts with one Virtual Payment Address. However, you have to set one default Bank Account for that Virtual Payment Address.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'I have more than one account with Bank(s), do I need separate virtual payment addresses for each of these accounts?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: I have more than one account with Bank(s), do I need separate virtual payment addresses for each of these accounts?
;
Fund DetailYou can either link both accounts to a single VPA or you can assign a separate VPA for each account. In the former, please ensure you have appropriately chosen which account you would like to use as the default account to get credit.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'I am able to see accounts which do not belong to me. What should I do?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: I am able to see accounts which do not belong to me. What should I do?
;
Fund DetailIt might be the case that your mobile number is mistakenly registered against the account number in question. Please contact the respective bank whose account is visible.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What if I enter the UPI PIN wrong for more than 3 attempts?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What if I enter the UPI PIN wrong for more than 3 attempts?
;
Fund DetailUPI PIN will be block permanently. You have to regenerate New UPI-PIN by using your debit card credential along with OTP sent by issuer bank.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'If I forgot UPI PIN, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: If I forgot UPI PIN, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
;
Fund DetailYou have to select SET/RESET UPI PIN option through UPI Application and require to put your last 6 six digits of debit card and expiry date along with OTP password which will be sent on registered mobile number from issuer bank.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'If I forgot Login PIN, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: If I forgot Login PIN, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
;
Fund DetailIn this case, click on forgot Login PIN, option is available on the login page. Now, on the next screen you will be asked to enter:
Question and answers which was set at the time of registration.
Now, after Answer and question, App will prompt to set New 4 digits Login PIN.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'If I forgot Question & Answers, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: If I forgot Question & Answers, what will be the procedure and details required for it?
;
Fund DetailIn this case, you have to select forgot Question & Answers option, available on forgot Login PIN page.
Enter registered email ID. An OTP will be sent on the entered email ID (valid for 10 Min)
Enter OTP and Submit.', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'What is MMID?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: What is MMID?
;
Fund DetailMobile Money Identifier (MMID) is a seven digits random number issued by the bank upon registration. Remitter (customer who wants to send money) and Beneficiary (customer who wants to receive the money) should have this MMID for doing these interbank funds transfer.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Can I put a stop payment request for funds transferred by UPI?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Can I put a stop payment request for funds transferred by UPI?
;
Fund DetailNo, once the payment is initiated, it cannot be stopped.

', 'file_chunk_index': 0}

{'Fund': 'Does the customer need to register a beneficiary before transferring funds through UPI? What details of beneficiary will be required?
', 'Fund Detail': 'Fund: Does the customer need to register a beneficiary before transferring funds through UPI? What details of beneficiary will be required?
;
